init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You decide to take a chance.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You try to brush it off again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're not sure why, but you're not afraid.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You get home, and your mother is there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You get in the car, and she drives you there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're not worried, but you are a little nervous.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You wake up in a hospital bed, your mother is there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The swelling is gone, and you're breathing normally.
